Counting the Nodes
Given the root of a tree A with each node having a certain value, find the count of nodes with more value than all its ancestor.



Problem Constraints
1 <= Number of Nodes <= 200000

1 <= Value of Nodes <= 2000000000



Input Format
The first and only argument of input is a tree node.



Output Format
Return a single integer denoting the count of nodes that have more value than all of its ancestors.



Example Input
Input 1:

 
     3
Input 2:

 
    4
   / \
  5   2
     / \
    3   6


Example Output
Output 1:

 1 
Output 2:

 3
 SOLUTION 
 
    static int ans=0;
    public int solve(TreeNode A) {  
           this.ans=0;
            return inorder(A,0);
        
    }

    int inorder(TreeNode root,int mx){
        
        if(root==null)
        return 0;
        int curmax=Math.max(root.val,mx);
        this.ans=inorder(root.left,curmax)+inorder(root.right,curmax);
        if(root.val>mx){
            ans++;
        }
        return ans;
    }
